review_blob: This is one of the best pale ales that Ive tried. An uncharacteristic thick head, and very smooth texture. Just a hint of bitterness, but not enough to be distracting. This one will probably become a regular in my fridge.

I couldnt get a good head going on this one, mustve been a bad pour. Anyways, smells potently of coffee and a strong but not over powering chocolate taste (the carbonation combines with it nicely). The bodys not too heavy, I could easily have more than one in a sitting.

Really delicious brew, a great oatmeal stout. The head is a nice beige and has a alluring burnt coffee aroma. Its dark, pushing black and tastes of chocolate and hints of caramel. Well balanced with a nice finish.
A satisfying, sweet wheat beer. Im not big on the type, but this one was different enough to peak my interest. Cloudy pour, but a decent brew.

Too bitter I think, I feel it covered the overall flavor. I didnt really pick up on a specific aroma, generic overall. On the plus side, it was pretty smooth. Im not into wheats and this is no different.
When poured right it has a near perfect appearance for a porter. Its smooth and creamy, tasting of coffee and chocolate. Just my type, really.
Has a decent kick to it, probably from cinnamon. Toffee is present as well, but not so prevalent. A good color thats slightly darker than your normal amber. Good malts and a decent aroma.
This is one of my go to brews. Darker than a pale ale, and more flavor really. Something of a nutty aroma with a darker finish. Not so smooth, but does the job.
For starters it has a very nice aroma, and the color is exactly what Im looking for in an amber. Complex taste, as well, a hint of blonde behind the spices.
The first pale ale to really catch my attention. Distinguishing taste from other pale ales, bitter but not too much so. Theres citrus in there, too.
Pretty satisfied with this purchase, though a bit pricey. Has an interesting cinnamon taste, but very much smells of pumpkin. Not much a head, but as are ambers.
The color is absolutely perfect. Rich flavor, but not overpowering really. And though it is a porter I didnt find it as filling. The head is a nice beige and has a coffee/toasted scent.
